article.headline: UNLV 73, Cent. Michigan 47
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Tre'Von Willis scored 15 points to lead UNLV to a 73-47 victory over Central Michigan on Thursday night. Justin Hawkins had 13 points and three steals, and Oscar Bellfield added 11 points and five assists for the Rebels (12-2). Trey Zeigler had 16 points, and Jalin Thomas added 11 points and 11 rebounds for Central Michigan (3-10). UNLV took control with a 14-2 run that gave them a 52-33 lead midway through the second half. The Chippewas had 25 turnovers, which the Rebels converted into 31 points. Quintrell Thomas had eight rebounds for UNLV.
